# Svelte Counter Component

Here's a simple counter component:

```svelte
<script>
  let count = 0;

  function increment() {
    count++;
  }

  function decrement() {
    count--;
  }

  function reset() {
    count = 0;
  }
</script>

<div class="counter">
  <h1>Counter: {count}</h1>

  <div class="buttons">
    <button on:click={decrement}>Decrement</button>
    <button on:click={increment}>Increment</button>
    <button on:click={reset}>Reset</button>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .counter {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  .buttons {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  button {
    padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: #007bff;
    color: white;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
  }

  button:hover {
    background-color: #0056b3;
  }

  button:active {
    transform: scale(0.98);
  }
</style>
```

## Alternative: More Compact Version

```svelte
<script>
  let count = 0;
</script>

<div class="counter">
  <button on:click={() => count--}>-</button>
  <span>{count}</span>
  <button on:click={() => count++}>+</button>
</div>

<style>
  .counter {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    align-items: center;
  }

  button {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  span {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    min-width: 50px;
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
```

## With Props (Reusable)

```svelte
<script>
  export let initialValue = 0;
  export let step = 1;

  let count = initialValue;
</script>

<div class="counter">
  <button on:click={() => count -= step}>-{step}</button>
  <span>{count}</span>
  <button on:click={() => count += step}>+{step}</button>
</div>

<!-- Usage in parent component -->
<!-- <Counter initialValue={10} step={5} /> -->
```

## Key Svelte Features Used

- **Reactive variables**: `let count = 0` automatically updates the DOM
- **Event handlers**: `on:click` directive
- **Scoped styles**: CSS is automatically scoped to the component
- **Exported props**: `export let` makes values configurable

Choose the version that best fits your needs! The first is most feature-rich, the second is minimal, and the third is most reusable.

